16 nonprofit organizations, and Smyrna Library to expand access to literacy resources and
17 educational support; and
18 WHEREAS, these initiatives have led to measurable improvements in reading proficiency,
19 creating greater opportunities for academic success and career development; and
20 WHEREAS, the dedication and hard work of Cobb Collaborative and its partners serve as
21 an inspiration to others, demonstrating the power of community-driven solutions to address
22 literacy challenges.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
24 congratulate and commend the Georgia Reads Community Award recipients, particularly
25 Cobb Collaborative, for their exemplary service and unwavering commitment to improving
26 literacy in their communities.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
28 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Cobb
29 Collaborative.
